The image presents a graph with the x-axis labeled "Digital input code" and the y-axis labeled "Differential linearity error". The graph displays the relationship between the digital input code (DAC) and the differential linearity error, represented by the number of channels shown on the external reference.

There are six channels visible in the graph, with three channels being shown for DAC57, 10-bit, and 40-bit inputs. The x-axis shows the DAC input codes, while the y-axis displays the corresponding differential linearity errors.
